template:docs/timeline.title: Timeline
template:docs/timeline.text: Timeline To generate timeline for events Simple Timeline A([ Ember.Object.create({ status: 'complete', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 1', content: 'Message 1', open: false }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'active', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 2', content: 'Message 2', open: false }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'inactive', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 3', content: 'Message 3', open: true }) ]) Complex Timeline A([Ember.Object.create({ status: 'complete', datetime: 1551161632, title: { component: 'custom-timeline-title', componentArgs: {} }, content: { component: 'custom-timeline-content', componentArgs: {} }, open: true }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'active', datetime: 1551161632, title: { component: 'custom-timeline-title', componentArgs: {} }, content: { component: 'custom-timeline-content', componentArgs: {} }, open: false }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'inactive', datetime: 1551161632, title: { component: 'custom-timeline-title', componentArgs: {} }, content: { component: 'custom-timeline-content', componentArgs: { message: 'hello' } }, open: false })]) Custom Simple Timeline A([ Ember.Object.create({ status: 'complete', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 1', content: 'Message 1', open: false }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'active', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 2', content: 'Message 2', open: false }), Ember.Object.create({ status: 'inactive', datetime: 1551161632, title: 'Title 3', content: 'Message 3', open: true }) ]) .custom-timeline { .s-timeline-event { .s-timeline-event-datetime { .axis { &.custom-data-active-state { &::before { background: #DF3D11; } } } .custom-data-active-state { &::after { border-color: #DF3D11; background-color: #DF3D11; } } } } } Property Description Type Default events This describes the data for the timeline events Ember.A / Object A([]) / [] ascending This describes the data displayed to be ascending Boolean true custom This describes the timeline should display custom states Boolean false customStates This describes the custom state definition Object {}
